### git-cliff Release Automation
**Templates**: `~/.claude/tools/git-cliff/templates/` (cliff.toml, cliff-release-notes.toml, cz.toml.template)

**AI Agent Workflow** (zero-config, AI-driven):
```bash
# Prerequisites: cargo, uvx, gh CLI

# Pre-flight: Workspace State Analysis (AI-driven)
git status --short --untracked-files=all > /tmp/git_status.txt
git diff --stat > /tmp/diff_unstaged.txt
git diff --cached --stat > /tmp/diff_staged.txt

# AI Decision Logic:
#   - Build artifacts (*.whl, *.log, target/, __pycache__/) ‚Üí .gitignore
#   - Source files (*.rs, *.py, *.toml, *.md) ‚Üí git add
#   - Modified tracked session files ‚Üí git add
#   - Sensitive (.env, *credentials*, *secret*, *.pem, *.key) ‚Üí NEVER add, warn
#   - Existing .gitignore patterns ‚Üí skip
git add [AI-selected files]
git diff --cached --stat

# 1) Auto-install git-cliff
command -v git-cliff >/dev/null || cargo install git-cliff

# 2) Initialize configs from templates
for f in cliff.toml cliff-release-notes.toml .cz.toml; do
  [ ! -f "$f" ] && [ -f ~/.claude/tools/git-cliff/templates/${f%.toml.template}.toml ] && \
    cp ~/.claude/tools/git-cliff/templates/${f%.toml.template}.toml ./$f
done

# 3) Parse project version (Cargo.toml, package.json, or default)
if [ -f Cargo.toml ]; then
  VERSION=$(grep '^version = ' Cargo.toml | head -1 | cut -d'"' -f2)
elif [ -f package.json ]; then
  VERSION=$(grep '"version"' package.json | head -1 | cut -d'"' -f4)
else
  VERSION="0.1.0"
fi

# 4) Sync .cz.toml with project version
[ -f .cz.toml ] && [ -n "$VERSION" ] && \
  sed -i.bak "s/^version = .*/version = \"$VERSION\"/" .cz.toml && rm .cz.toml.bak

# 5) Commit (AI synthesizes $MSG from git diff --cached)
uvx --from commitizen cz check --message "$MSG"
git commit -m "$MSG"

# 6) Version bump + changelog
uvx --from commitizen cz bump --yes
git-cliff --config cliff.toml --output CHANGELOG.md
git-cliff --config cliff-release-notes.toml --latest --output RELEASE_NOTES.md
git add CHANGELOG.md RELEASE_NOTES.md && git commit --amend --no-edit

# 7) Push with tags
git push --follow-tags

# 8) Surface CI (optional: gh run watch for streaming)
gh run view --web

# 9) GitHub Release
TAG="v$(grep '^version = ' .cz.toml | cut -d'"' -f2)"
gh release create "$TAG" --verify-tag --title "$(basename $(pwd)) $TAG" -F RELEASE_NOTES.md

# 10) Telemetry
echo "üì¶ Release: https://github.com/$(gh repo view --json nameWithOwner -q .nameWithOwner)/releases/tag/$TAG"
echo "üîó CI Run: $(gh run list --limit 1 --json url --jq '.[0].url')"
echo "üìù Commit: $(git rev-parse HEAD)"
```

**Notes**:
- AI agent analyzes workspace state and intelligently stages changes
- Auto-syncs version from Cargo.toml/package.json to .cz.toml
- Commitizen handles SemVer validation, git-cliff generates changelogs
- Use Git LFS for large binaries

